"Grantham, Lincolnshire, England":"Grantham, Lincolnshire, England","Spalding,Lincolnshire,England.":"Spalding, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ramera","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Italian: habitational name from a place in Sicily named Càmera.","Portuguese (mainly Azores): variant of <b>Câmara</b> (see   Camara  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Camara","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Manuel, Carlos, Jose, Jorge, Ana, Francisco, Luis, Pedro, Juan, Alejandro, Armando, Augusto.  Portuguese Joao, Duarte, Joaquim, Afonso, Heitor, Manoel, Marcio, Messias.  African/Muslim Mamadou, Boubacar, Mamady, Aboubacar, Amadou, Bakary, Fatou, Ousmane, Babacar, Balla, Brahima, Hamidou.","Spanish (<b>Cámara</b>) and Portuguese (<b>Câmara</b>): from Spanish <i>cámara</i>, Portuguese <i>câmara</i> ‘(main) room’ (from Latin <i>camera</i>), hence an occupational name for a courtier or servant who had access to the private living quarters of a king or noble.","West African (mainly Guinea, Senegal, Mali, and Ivory Coast): from the name of the Kamara clan of the Mandinka and closely related Soninke peoples; see   Kamara   1."]}]},{"name":"Lucia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Feminine form of the old Roman given name <i>Lucius</i>, which is probably a derivative of Latin <i>lux</i> ‘light’. The girl's name is common in Italy and elsewhere, and is found as a learned, Latinate doublet of   Lucy   in England.  St Lucia  of Syracuse, who was martyred in  304 , was a very popular saint in the Middle Ages; she is often represented in medieval art as blinded and with her eyes on a platter, but the tradition that she had her eyes put out is probably based on nothing more than the association between light and eyes."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Mercia","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["elaboration of   Mercy  , coinciding in form with the name of the Anglo-Saxon kingdom of Mercia, which dominated England during the 8th century under its king, Offa."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Lucia Mercia Ramera was born in 1070, in Spalding, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Alan de Graham. She died on 26 June 1144, in Chester, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1070–26 June 1144":"1070–26. juuni 1144","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1097–1139":"1097–1139","1070–1144":"1070–1144","1080":"1080","Abt 1097":"umbes 1097","1139":"1139","26 June 1144":"26. juuni 1144","Aft 1139":"pärast 1139","1144":"1144","1097":"1097","1130":"1130","about 1130":"umbes 1130","1070":"1070","Chester,Cheshire,England.":"Chester, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dalkeith, Midlothian, Scotland":"Dalkeith, Midlothian, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Grantham, Lincolnshire, England":"Grantham, Lincolnshire, England","Spalding,Lincolnshire,England.":"Spalding, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1070–26 June 1144":"1070–26. kesäkuuta 1144","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1097–1139":"1097–1139","1070–1144":"1070–1144","1080":"1080","Abt 1097":"noin 1097","1139":"1139","26 June 1144":"26. kesäkuuta 1144","Aft 1139":"1139 jälkeen","1144":"1144","1097":"1097","1130":"1130","about 1130":"noin 1130","1070":"1070","Chester,Cheshire,England.":"Chester, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dalkeith, Midlothian, Scotland":"Dalkeith, Midlothian, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Grantham, Lincolnshire, England":"Grantham, Lincolnshire, England","Spalding,Lincolnshire,England.":"Spalding, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1070–26 June 1144":"1070–26 juin 1144","1080–1130":"1080–1130","1097–1139":"1097–1139","1070–1144":"1070–1144","1080":"1080","Abt 1097":"environ 1097","1139":"1139","26 June 1144":"26 juin 1144","Aft 1139":